1296 auto & functors = _functors[tid];
1297 auto it = functors.find("wraps_" + name);
1298 if (it != functors.end())
1299 {
1300 // We have this functor already. If it's a null functor, we want to replace it with the valid
1301 // functor we have now. If it's not then we'll add a new entry into the multimap and then we'll
1302 // error later if a user requests a functor because their request is ambiguous. This is the
1303 // reason that the functors container is a multimap: for nice error messages
1304 auto * const existing_wrapper_base =
1305 added_functor_is_ad ? std::get<2>(it->second).get() : std::get<1>(it->second).get();
1306 auto * const existing_wrapper = dynamic_cast<Moose::Functor<T> *>(existing_wrapper_base);
1307 if (existing_wrapper && existing_wrapper->template wrapsType<Moose::NullFunctor<T>>())
1308 {
1309 // Sanity check
1310 auto [request_info_it, request_info_end_it] = functor_to_request_info.equal_range(name);
1311 if (request_info_it == request_info_end_it)
1312 mooseError("We are wrapping a NullFunctor but we don't have any unfilled functor request "
1313 "info. This doesn't make sense.");
1314
1315 // Check for valid requests
1316 while (request_info_it != request_info_end_it)
1317 {
1318 auto & [requested_functor_is_ad, requestor_is_ad] = request_info_it->second;
1319 if (!requested_functor_is_ad && requestor_is_ad && added_functor_is_ad)
1320 mooseError("We are requesting a non-AD functor from an AD object, but the true functor "
1321 "is AD. This means we could be dropping important derivatives. We will not "
1322 "allow this");
1323 // We're going to eventually check whether we've fulfilled all functor requests and our
1324 // check will be that the multimap is empty. This request is fulfilled, so erase it from the
1325 // map now
1326 request_info_it = functor_to_request_info.erase(request_info_it);
1327 }
1328
1329 // Ok we didn't have the functor before, so we will add it now

1331 added_functor_is_ad ? SubProblem::TrueFunctorIs::AD : SubProblem::TrueFunctorIs::NONAD;
1332 existing_wrapper->assign(functor);
1333 // Finally we create the non-AD or AD complement of the just added functor
1334 if constexpr (added_functor_is_ad)
1335 {
1336 typedef typename MetaPhysicL::RawType<T>::value_type NonADType;
1337 auto * const existing_non_ad_wrapper_base = std::get<1>(it->second).get();
1338 auto * const existing_non_ad_wrapper =
1339 dynamic_cast<Moose::Functor<NonADType> *>(existing_non_ad_wrapper_base);
1340 mooseAssert(existing_non_ad_wrapper->template wrapsType<Moose::NullFunctor<NonADType>>(),
1341 "Both members of pair should have been wrapping a NullFunctor");
1342 existing_non_ad_wrapper->assign(
1343 std::make_unique<Moose::RawValueFunctor<NonADType>>(functor));
1344 }
1345 else
1346 {
1347 typedef typename Moose::ADType<T>::type ADType;
1348 auto * const existing_ad_wrapper_base = std::get<2>(it->second).get();

1350 dynamic_cast<Moose::Functor<ADType> *>(existing_ad_wrapper_base);
1351 mooseAssert(existing_ad_wrapper->template wrapsType<Moose::NullFunctor<ADType>>(),
1352 "Both members of pair should have been wrapping a NullFunctor");
1353 existing_ad_wrapper->assign(std::make_unique<Moose::ADWrapperFunctor<ADType>>(functor));
1354 }
1355 return;
1356 }
1357 }
1358
1359 // We are a new functor, create the opposite ADType one and store it with other functors
1360 if constexpr (added_functor_is_ad)
1361 {
1362 typedef typename MetaPhysicL::RawType<T>::value_type NonADType;
1363 auto new_non_ad_wrapper = std::make_unique<Moose::Functor<NonADType>>(
1364 std::make_unique<Moose::RawValueFunctor<NonADType>>(functor));
1365 auto new_ad_wrapper = std::make_unique<Moose::Functor<T>>(functor);

1367 std::make_tuple(SubProblem::TrueFunctorIs::AD,
1368 std::move(new_non_ad_wrapper),
1369 std::move(new_ad_wrapper)));
1370 }
1371 else
1372 {
1373 typedef typename Moose::ADType<T>::type ADType;
1374 auto new_non_ad_wrapper = std::make_unique<Moose::Functor<T>>((functor));
1375 auto new_ad_wrapper = std::make_unique<Moose::Functor<ADType>>(
1376 std::make_unique<Moose::ADWrapperFunctor<ADType>>(functor));
1377 _functors[tid].emplace("wraps_" + name,
1378 std::make_tuple(SubProblem::TrueFunctorIs::NONAD,
1379 std::move(new_non_ad_wrapper),
1380 std::move(new_ad_wrapper)));

◆ updateMesh() [1/2]

void DisplacedProblem::updateMesh ( bool  mesh_changing = false)
virtual

Copy the solutions on the undisplaced systems to the displaced systems and reinitialize the geometry search data and Dirac kernel information due to mesh displacement.

The parameter mesh_changing indicates whether this method is getting called because of mesh changes, e.g. due to mesh adaptivity. If mesh_changing we need to renitialize the GeometricSearchData instead of simply update. Reinitialization operations are a super-set of update operations. Reinitialization for example re-generates neighbor nodes in NearestNodeLocators, while update does not. Additionally we do not want to use the undisplaced mesh solution because it may be out-of-sync, whereas our displaced mesh solution should be in the correct state after getting restricted/prolonged in EquationSystems::reinit

Definition at line 245 of file DisplacedProblem.C.

246{
247 TIME_SECTION("updateMesh", 3, "Updating Displaced Mesh");
248
249 // If the mesh is changing, we are probably performing adaptivity. In that case, we do *not* want
250 // to use the undisplaced mesh solution because it may be out-of-sync, whereas our displaced mesh
251 // solution should be in the correct state after getting restricted/prolonged in
252 // EquationSystems::reinit (must have been called before this method)
253 if (!mesh_changing)
254 syncSolutions();
255
256 for (const auto nl_sys_num : index_range(_displaced_nl))
257 _nl_solution[nl_sys_num] = _displaced_nl[nl_sys_num]->sys().solution.get();
258 _aux_solution = _displaced_aux->sys().solution.get();
259
260 // If the displaced mesh has been serialized to one processor (as
261 // may have occurred if it was used for Exodus output), then we need
262 // the reference mesh to be also. For that matter, did anyone
263 // somehow serialize the whole mesh? Hopefully not but let's avoid
264 // causing errors if so.
265 if (_mesh.getMesh().is_serial() && !this->refMesh().getMesh().is_serial())
266 this->refMesh().getMesh().allgather();
267
268 if (_mesh.getMesh().is_serial_on_zero() && !this->refMesh().getMesh().is_serial_on_zero())
269 this->refMesh().getMesh().gather_to_zero();
270
271 UpdateDisplacedMeshThread udmt(_mproblem, *this);
272
273 // We displace all nodes, not just semilocal nodes, because
274 // parallel-inconsistent mesh geometry makes libMesh cry.
275 NodeRange node_range(_mesh.getMesh().nodes_begin(),
276 _mesh.getMesh().nodes_end(),
277 /*grainsize=*/1);
278
279 Threads::parallel_reduce(node_range, udmt);
280 // Displacement of the mesh has invalidated the point locator data (e.g. bounding boxes)
281 _mesh.getMesh().clear_point_locator();
282
283 // The mesh has changed. Face information normals, areas, etc. must be re-calculated
284 if (haveFV())
285 _mesh.setupFiniteVolumeMeshData();
286
287 for (auto & disp_nl : _displaced_nl)
288 disp_nl->update(false);
289 _displaced_aux->update(false);
290
291 // Update the geometric searches that depend on the displaced mesh. This call can end up running
292 // NearestNodeThread::operator() which has a throw inside of it. We need to catch it and make sure
293 // it's propagated to all processes before updating the point locator because the latter requires
294 // communication
295 try
296 {
297 // We may need to re-run geometric operations like SecondaryNeighborhoodTread if, for instance,
298 // we have performed mesh adaptivity
299 if (mesh_changing)
300 _geometric_search_data.reinit();
301 else
302 _geometric_search_data.update();
303 }
304 catch (MooseException & e)
305 {
306 _mproblem.setException(e.what());
307 }
308
309 // The below call will throw an exception on all processes if any of our processes had an
310 // exception above. This exception will be caught higher up the call stack and the error message
311 // will be printed there
312 _mproblem.checkExceptionAndStopSolve(/*print_message=*/false);
313
314 // Since the Mesh changed, update the PointLocator object used by DiracKernels.
315 _dirac_kernel_info.updatePointLocator(_mesh);
316}
